    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Vienna, 20 July 1551)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>1. He understood from Nádasdy’s letter of the third of this month that
                            Nádasdy’s matters are dragging on; the King has done everything he can
                            and will do so in the future to make sure there is no delay. If Miklós
                            Báthori saves them, Oláh will send someone else to support Báthori. He
                            will understand the rest from the King’s letter to András (Bonaventura)
                            Báthori. 2. He has forwarded Nádasdy’s letter to Orsolya Kanizsai.
                            Nádasdy should find out if he likes white wine. András (Bonaventura)
                            Báthori will tell him the news.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Salutem plurimam et servitiorum meorum commendationem, Spectabilis et
                    Magnifice Domine et Frater Observandissime! </p>
                <p>[1.] Ex litteris Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae tertia huius
                        datis<note type="critic">We do not know this letter.</note> intellexi
                    negotia istic adhuc protrahi; spero omnia feliciter successura. Hinc a
                        <persName>maiestate regia</persName>, domino nostro clementissimo nihil
                    praetermissum est hactenus, neque praetermittetur, quod negotia illa remorari
                    posset, si istinc bona fide agantur. Si <persName>Nicolaus
                        Bathori</persName><note type="critic">Miklós Báthori of Ecsed (ca.1520–1584)
                        was the son of András Báthori (†1534) and brother of András (Bonaventura)
                        Báthori, who was always loyal to the Habsburgs. Miklós was loyal to King
                        John Sigismund I at first, then in 1561 he changed sides. From 1568 until
                        his death, he was Judge Royal <hi rend="italic">(iudex curiae)</hi>, and <hi
                            rend="italic">ispán</hi> of Szabolcs and Szatmár counties. See <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Baráth</hi> 2008, especially 35.</note> eruet vos a
                    malis, mittemus et alium, qui ei sit adiumento. Verum omnia intelligent
                    Dominationes Vestrae ex litteris regiis nunc ad dominum <persName>capitaneum
                        generalem</persName><note type="critic">András (Bonaventura) Báthori.</note>
                    datis. Exspecto itaque iam in dies singulos a Dominationibus Vestris finem bonum
                    omnium negotiorum. </p>
                <p>[2.] Litteras Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae misi ad dominam meam
                    observandissimam, dominam <persName>coniugem</persName><note type="critic"
                        >Orsolya Kanizsai.</note> suam carissimam, quae feliciter valet. Post
                    discessum Dominationis Vestrae Magnificae parum abfuit, quin per illum amicum
                    nostrum cum suis cohaerentibus indicaret in interitum, quod Deus a me inmerito
                    capiti illius, si meretur, inmittat. Dominatio Vestra expiscetur, an <choice>
                        <orig>albus</orig>
                        <supplied>album</supplied>
                    </choice> cupiat et ambiat vinum de <placeName>Farnad</placeName>.<note
                        type="critic">Farná was known for its wine, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Vályi</hi> 1796, 638.</note> Ego illi auxilio esse possem, qua de re,
                    si quid intellexerat, faciat me, rogo, Dominatio Vestra certiorem. Nova, quae
                    habui, intelliget Dominatio Vestra Magnifica a <persName>domino
                        generali</persName>. Eandem feliciter valere opto, cui servitia mea
                    commendo.</p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Wienna</placeName> 20. Iulii anno 1551.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Frater et servitor Agriensis etc. manu propria</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Spectabili et magnifico domino comiti Thomae de Nadasd perpetuo terrae
                    Fogaras et comitatus Castriferrei comiti, iudici curiae et consiliario regiae
                    maiestatis ac supremo regni Hungariae capitaneo etc. domino et fratri nobis
                    observandissimo.</p>
                
                
            </div>
        </body>
